Proposal: Demand for Conservation and Repair Scheme for Minor Irrigation (Water Conservation) Projects with an irrigation potential of 101 to 250 hectares No. ZH-5, Account Head 4702 A055 has been budgeted at Rs. 60.00 crore in the year 2024-25. Now, as per the reference circulars of the Department of Finance, the following decision has been taken on the proposal for seeking reference funds from the funds made available under the revised estimate limit.
Decision: Co. P. Bandara Borgaon, Sillod Taluka, Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar District
Total for payment of pending payments for maintenance and repair works of the project at Bajar.
Rs. 58.85 Lakhs (Rupees Fifty-eight Lakhs Eighty-five Thousand Only) As Funded
Through this, government approval is being provided for distribution.
The aforesaid funds are being disbursed subject to the following terms and conditions: -

Funds should be disbursed on a payment basis, ensuring quality of repair work, b) not exceeding the sanctioned price, c) if funds remain unutilized for any reason, the amount should be immediately returned to the government without any reciprocal distribution, e) strictly follow the guidelines in the relevant circular of the Department of Finance regarding fund disbursement.
e) Ensure that the procedures and instructions laid down under the Government decision on the Mukhyamantri Jal Sanrakshan Yojana are complied with.
3. The amount disbursed by it to the Regional Water Conservation Officer, Mrid and
The respective districts under their jurisdiction were taken over by the Water Conservation Department, G. Sambhajinagar.
The water should be distributed to the conservation authorities expeditiously.

2024-25 to be subtracted from the approved provision for this financial year.

Copies of the same should be made available to the government along with a certificate of completion of the repair.

The Office of the Water Conservation Officer shall be the Office of the Additional Commissioner and the Chief Engineer, Soil and
Water Conservation, Regional Area, Pune will be the coordinating authority for these matters.
